    "body": "The string is always URI formatted. Could you use\nhttps://github.com/cpp-netlib/uri for the string parsing?\n\nOn Thu, Mar 10, 2016, 12:32 AM Pavel Odintsov notifications@github.com\nwrote:\n\n> Hello!\n> \n> I'm speaking about C++ code. So my API is deeply relying on customer's IP\n> address and in each API call I should so something like this:\n> \n>    grpc::Status GetExternalAddress(grpc::ServerContext\\* context,\n>                               const fastmitigation::BlankRequest\\* request,\n>                               fastmitigation::ExternalAddressReply\\* reply) override {\n>         std::vectorstd::string splitted_peer;\n>         std::string peer_raw = context->peer();\n> \n> ```\n>     boost::split(splitted_peer, peer_raw, boost::is_any_of(\":\"), boost::token_compress_on);\n> \n>     if (splitted_peer.size() != 3) {\n>         logger << log4cpp::Priority::ERROR << \"Could not parse peer address. Got \" << splitted_peer.size()\n>                << \" instead 3 \";\n> \n>         return grpc::Status(grpc::StatusCode::INVALID_ARGUMENT, \"Could not parse peer address\");\n>     }\n> \n>     std::string protocol_family = splitted_peer[0];\n>     std::string client_ip = splitted_peer[1];\n> \n>     if (protocol_family != \"ipv4\") {\n>         logger << log4cpp::Priority::ERROR\n>                << \"We support only IPv4 client but got client with protocol: \" << protocol_family;\n>         return grpc::Status(grpc::StatusCode::INVALID_ARGUMENT, \"We support only IPv4 client but got client with protocol: \" + protocol_family);\n>     }\n> \n>    # start processing\n> ```\n> \n> }\n> \n> As you can see there are so much code for very popular task. Could you add\n> some way for simpler extracting of peer IP address without not very\n> reliable string parsing?\n> \n> â€”\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub\n> https://github.com/grpc/grpc/issues/5693.\n"
  },
